This project sets up the User Acceptance Tests (UAT) environment for WebEssentials.

The UAT are based on the requirements and are executed by a "Ruby":http://www.ruby-lang.org library
called cucumber":http://cukes.info/


# Installation

0. Install vim, git and curl to install and configure other tools later:
	sudo apt-get install vim git curl
1. Install PhantomJS
See https://github.com/jonleighton/poltergeist#installing-phantomjs
2. Install XMLlib header for nokogiri requirements
	sudo apt-get install libxslt-dev libxml2-dev
See http://nokogiri.org/tutorials/installing_nokogiri.html
3. Install RVM. See http://rvm.io
This also installs Ruby 1.9.3 automatically.
4. Install bundler
  gem install bundler
5. Run `bundle` to install all ruby libraries and dependencies
6. Run `cucumber` to run the tests

Please see `config/cucumber.yml` to change the target website eg. if you want to tests another project.

If you want to run only particular feature tests call `cucumber` like this

	cucumber features/smoke_test.feature


